cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Squishy, please cite the edition you ran against."
title: "Squishy: a curated 2026 compression benchmark corpus and score"
abstract: >-
  Squishy is a successor to the Silesia corpus: one curated set of real,
  redistributable files spanning kinds and sizes, plus a single citable headline
  metric — the Squishy Score, the geometric mean of per-file compression ratio
  over the whole corpus (one vote per file), reported with a byte-weighted corpus
  bits-per-byte. Editions are versioned and dated;
  each is frozen and assigned a DOI.
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Danger
    given-names: Jack
version: "Squishy-2026"
# date-released is the Squishy-2026 edition release date. If the owner freezes on a
# different day, update this together with the DOI line below (the only post-mint edits).
date-released: 2026-06-25
license-url: "https://github.com/JackDanger/squishy-corpus/blob/main/build/meta/LICENSE-MANIFEST.csv"
url: "https://github.com/JackDanger/squishy-corpus"
keywords:
  - compression
  - benchmark
  - corpus
  - data compression
  - lossless
# At the Squishy-2026 freeze, zenodo-deposit.py mints the DOI; fill BOTH lines below with the
# concrete record so citations resolve to the immutable Zenodo deposit, not the
# mutable repo (then drop these comments):
# identifiers:
#   - type: doi
#     value: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"        # the Squishy-2026 edition record
#     description: "Squishy-2026 edition (frozen corpus + score)"
# preferred-citation: use the DOI above; the repo URL is the development source.
